(110, 1, '2018-12-08 01:27:15', '2018-12-08 09:27:15', 'This was designed for an (unfortunately) theoretical wolf sanctuary located to the north of Vancouver Island.\r\n\r\nI made several very rough sketches before developing an idea in Illustrator. I knew I needed to involve the wolf in some way, so first I traced the outline of a wolf’s head to use as a scalable vector graphic.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-35 aligncenter\" src=\"http://localhost/dequalsmcsquared/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/RCWS-outline-300x212.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"212\" />\r\n\r\n<!--more-->The initial concept was a rocky coastline in the top right corner and a wolf’s head off the coast line in the ‘water’, but the idea didn’t convey very well.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-37 aligncenter\" src=\"http://localhost/dequalsmcsquared/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/RCWS-roughs-300x182.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"182\" />\r\n\r\nI chose Athelas Bold, a serif font, for the sanctuary name and used Thonburi, a sans serif font, in all caps to explicitly state what Rocky Coast was.\r\n\r\nI needed to ground the logo with a better sense of place, so I resolved to incorporate Vancouver Island in the logo as well.  After outlining Vancouver Island, I switched the position of the wolf’s head, so it emerged as part of the island.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-34 alignright\" src=\"http://localhost/dequalsmcsquared/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/RCWS-full-300x181.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"181\" />\r\n\r\nThis logo can be used on business cards and stationary, company vehicles, or on hats, t-shirts, sweatshirts, and jackets, or as a watermark on advertising or postcards.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-33\" src=\"http://localhost/dequalsmcsquared/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/RCWF-watermark-200x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" />', 'Rocky Coast Wolf Sanctuary', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'rocky-coast', '', '', '2018-12-10 00:39:19', '2018-12-10 08:39:19', '', 0, 'http://localhost/dequalsmcsquared/?p=110', 5, 'post', '', 0),
